data.description: This charming home built in 1900, is ideally located a very short distance from downtown Cornelius with shopping, dining, and the Cain Center for the Arts! Featuring multiple covered rocking chair porches, period wood floors, 9.5-foot ceilings on the main level, 4 bedrooms and 3 full baths, this house sits on nearly .5 acres with privacy in the rear.  It's located in the NMX (Neighborhood Mixed Use) zone, which is for commercial, residential, and retail, with certain restrictions.  Though this house is currently listed as residential, several steps have been taken to make this a commercial property including installing a large concrete driveway with a gravel lot in the rear for minimum 5 cars, a handicap parking spot, handicap ramp, and bicycle parking as well.  In addition, the proposed lightrail would be right across the street with a stop nearby! With so many great things happening in Cornelius, you don't want to miss out on this rare opportunity! The possibilities are endless!
